After updating the microSD to this year’s competition, we put it into the roboRio 2.0 and connected it to the roboRio imager. Typed in our team number and clicked apply, from which the roboRio status LED started blinking and the imager gave an error.

After this, we re-flashed the microSD but the same error still occurs. How can we fix this issue?

When you updated your team number, did you do it by editing the startup settings or by reformatting the Rio?

We had a similar error where we used the “Format Target” setting on the Imaging Tool instead of the “Edit Startup Settings” option. After reflashing the SD Card with Balena Etcher and setting the team number properly, we had no issues.

Relevant Documentation: Imaging your roboRIO 2 — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation

Let me know if this helps.
